<subSubSection id="C37C6521FFE0FFFAFF4EA58377923107" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="562" pageId="5" pageNumber="560" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD936AAFFE0FFF8FF4EA583778534D9" blockId="5.[151,1436,1966,2027]" box="[151,757,1966,1991]" pageId="5" pageNumber="560">
<emphasis id="B912EAB8FFE0FFF8FF4EA583745934D8" bold="true" box="[151,297,1966,1991]" pageId="5" pageNumber="560">Description.</emphasis>
Length (including wings): male 
<quantity id="4C9E9B4FFFE0FFF8FD41A583778134D9" box="[664,753,1966,1991]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="560" unit="mm" value="6.5">6.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD936AAFFE0FFFBFF1EA5FE7110327B" blockId="5.[151,1436,1966,2027]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,151,357]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="561" pageId="5" pageNumber="560">
Crown straw colored, with black spot on either side of median line closer to eyes, one square spot in middle; face upper part gray with black round spot on either side of median line closer to median line; frontoclypeus mainly black, yellowish in middle, anteclypeus black, lora and gena brownish, antennal fossa brownish. Pronotum gray, with three triangular spots on anterior margin and one spot on either side of median line and several brown stripes closer to posterior margin. Scutellum dark yellow, with median stripes and basal triangles dark brown (
<figureCitation id="135D2A2FFFE3FFFBFABDA32975D1325F" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1726,1748]" captionTargetBox="[156,1436,199,1702]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1705]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Flexocerus sinuatus sp. nov. A, habitus of male, dorsal view; B, habitus of male, lateral view; C, head and thorax of male, dorsal view; D, face of male; E, head and thorax of female, dorsal view; F, face of female; G, habitus of female, dorsal view; H, habitus of female, lateral view. Idioceroides petaliformis sp. nov. I, habitus, dorsal view; J, habitus, lateral view; K, head and thorax, dorsal view; L, face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/245573/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="561">
Figs. 
<number id="3DAE248DFFE3FFFBFF4EA30575D1325F" box="[151,161,296,320]" pageId="6" pageNumber="561" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
K–L). Forewing hyaline with brown tinge, veins and apex of forewing dark brown, apex of clavus whitish. Mesepimeron black. Legs pale ochraceous, hind leg macrosetae brownish (
<figureCitation id="135D2A2FFFE3FFFBFC39A3617159327B" box="[992,1065,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1726,1748]" captionTargetBox="[156,1436,199,1702]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1705]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Flexocerus sinuatus sp. nov. A, habitus of male, dorsal view; B, habitus of male, lateral view; C, head and thorax of male, dorsal view; D, face of male; E, head and thorax of female, dorsal view; F, face of female; G, habitus of female, dorsal view; H, habitus of female, lateral view. Idioceroides petaliformis sp. nov. I, habitus, dorsal view; J, habitus, lateral view; K, head and thorax, dorsal view; L, face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/245573/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="561">
Figs. 
<number id="3DAE248DFFE3FFFBFBC6A3617159327B" box="[1055,1065,332,356]" pageId="6" pageNumber="561" value="1.0">
<date id="FFD8106AFFE3FFFBFBC6A3617159327B" box="[1055,1065,332,356]" pageId="6" pageNumber="561">1</date>
</number>
</figureCitation>
I–J).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF196622FFE3FFFBFF4EA5AE71FB34A7" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/245576/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="561" targetBox="[208,1385,417,1887]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph id="8BD936AAFFE3FFFBFF4EA5AE71FB34A7" blockId="6.[151,1435,1923,1976]" pageId="6" pageNumber="561">
<emphasis id="B912EAB8FFE3FFFBFF4EA5AE74663487" bold="true" box="[151,278,1923,1945]" pageId="6" pageNumber="561">FIGURE 4.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C664D29FFE3FFFBFEF9A5AE77513487" box="[288,545,1923,1944]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Idioceroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="561" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petaliformis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B912EAB8FFE3FFFBFEF9A5AE77513487" box="[288,545,1923,1944]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="561">Idioceroides petaliformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22157C3FFE3FFFBFDF5A5AE77F03487" box="[556,640,1923,1944]" pageId="6" pageNumber="561" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B912EAB8FFE3FFFBFDF5A5AE77F03487" bold="true" box="[556,640,1923,1944]" pageId="6" pageNumber="561">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
A, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, valve; C, connective, ventral view; D, aedeagus, lateral view; E, aedeagus, ventral view; F, style, lateral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BD936AAFFE2FFFAFF1EA2B5712D33E7" blockId="7.[151,1437,151,752]" pageId="7" pageNumber="562">
Face without short setae adjacent to corresponding eye; rostrum short, not reaching hind coxae. Pronotum rugose. Scutellum about as long as pronotum and crown together (
<figureCitation id="135D2A2FFFE2FFFAFC55A29176BC33CB" box="[908,972,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1726,1748]" captionTargetBox="[156,1436,199,1702]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1705]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Flexocerus sinuatus sp. nov. A, habitus of male, dorsal view; B, habitus of male, lateral view; C, head and thorax of male, dorsal view; D, face of male; E, head and thorax of female, dorsal view; F, face of female; G, habitus of female, dorsal view; H, habitus of female, lateral view. Idioceroides petaliformis sp. nov. I, habitus, dorsal view; J, habitus, lateral view; K, head and thorax, dorsal view; L, face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/245573/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="562">
Fig. 
<number id="3DAE248DFFE2FFFAFC18A29176BC33CB" box="[961,972,188,212]" pageId="7" pageNumber="562" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
K). 
<collectingCountry id="F371763AFFE2FFFAFC25A291714433CA" box="[1020,1076,188,213]" name="India" pageId="7" pageNumber="562">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibiae with 
<number id="3DAE248DFFE2FFFAFB67A291707433CB" box="[1214,1284,188,212]" pageId="7" pageNumber="562" value="23.0" valueMax="24.0" valueMin="22.0">22–24</number>
setae on row PD, 
<number id="3DAE248DFFE2FFFAFF10A2CD75A733E7" box="[201,215,224,248]" pageId="7" pageNumber="562" value="9.0">9</number>
setae on AD and 
<number id="3DAE248DFFE2FFFAFE47A2CD74CA33E7" box="[414,442,224,248]" pageId="7" pageNumber="562" value="12.0">12</number>
setae on row AV. Other characters as in generic description.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD936AAFFE2FFFAFF1EA32977923107" blockId="7.[151,1437,151,752]" pageId="7" pageNumber="562">
Male genitalia. Male pygofer elongate, broader in middle, compressed apically, with dense setae on lateral area, ventral margin convex. Subgenital plate broad, dorsal margin straight, ventral margin convex, with many setae on dorsal margin and lateral area, pointed apically (
<figureCitation id="135D2A2FFFE2FFFAFCC9A3617623327B" box="[784,851,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1923,1945]" captionTargetBox="[208,1385,417,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1397,409,1901]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Idioceroides petaliformis sp. nov. A, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, valve; C, connective, ventral view; D, aedeagus, lateral view; E, aedeagus, ventral view; F, style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/245576/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="562">
Fig. 
<number id="3DAE248DFFE2FFFAFC9DA3617623327B" box="[836,851,332,356]" pageId="7" pageNumber="562" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Valve broader than long, caudal margin rounded, shieldlike. Style with process on dorsal margin nearer base than apex; caudal part tapering apically, apex curved (
<figureCitation id="135D2A2FFFE2FFFAFF46A3B9759432B3" box="[159,228,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1923,1945]" captionTargetBox="[208,1385,417,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1397,409,1901]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Idioceroides petaliformis sp. nov. A, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, valve; C, connective, ventral view; D, aedeagus, lateral view; E, aedeagus, ventral view; F, style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/245576/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="562">
Fig. 
<number id="3DAE248DFFE2FFFAFF0DA3B9759432B3" box="[212,228,404,428]" pageId="7" pageNumber="562" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
F). Connective T-shaped, stem slender and long. Aedeagus with preatrium well developed, dorsal apodeme short; shaft evenly curved dorsad, with lateral preapical flange bearing two pairs of long distally projecting spines, dorsal surface with pair of long retrorse preapical spines, apex in lateral view with shorter spine projecting anterad; gonopore subapical on ventral surface.(
<figureCitation id="135D2A2FFFE2FFFAFD8AA3D277EE3107" box="[595,670,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1923,1945]" captionTargetBox="[208,1385,417,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1397,409,1901]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Idioceroides petaliformis sp. nov. A, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, valve; C, connective, ventral view; D, aedeagus, lateral view; E, aedeagus, ventral view; F, style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/245576/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="562">
Figs. 
<number id="3DAE248DFFE2FFFAFD56A02D77EE3107" box="[655,670,512,536]" pageId="7" pageNumber="562" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
D–E).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37C6521FFE2FFFAFF1EA00970023122" box="[199,1394,548,573]" pageId="7" pageNumber="562" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD936AAFFE2FFFAFF1EA00970023122" blockId="7.[151,1437,151,752]" box="[199,1394,548,573]" pageId="7" pageNumber="562">
<emphasis id="B912EAB8FFE2FFFAFF1EA009743E3122" bold="true" box="[199,334,548,573]" pageId="7" pageNumber="562">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet name refers to the flower like appearance of the aedeagus in ventral view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
